  "title": "CONTRACTS MANAGER",
  "description": "<p>Job Description</p><ul><li>Plan, lead and monitor progress and performance against the project plan</li><li>Manages day-to-day operational aspects of a project, which includes manpower planning, construction progress monitoring, preparation of master schedule and cost control</li><li>Take actions to deal with the results of delay, bad weather or emergencies at construction site</li><li>Liaise with clients, consultants, subcontractors and authorities in resolving site issues</li><li>Effectively applies safe and economical methodology enforces project standards</li><li>Recognised Degree in Civil Engineering or its equivalent</li><li>Minimum 10 years' construction experience in project/site management in construction industry</li><li>Must have working experiences in site construction management.</li><li>Completed relevant safety courses required by MOM</li><li>Independent, diligent, meticulous and highly motivated with excellent team spirit</li></ul>",
